(70, 8, 14, '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: .0001pt; line-height: 107%;\"><strong style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight: normal;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 11.0pt; line-height: 107%; font-family: \'Arial\',\'sans-serif\'; mso-fareast-font-family: Arial; color: #0070c0;\">Hepatitis A</span></strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: .0001pt; line-height: 107%;\"><strong style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight: normal;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 11.0pt; line-height: 107%; font-family: \'Arial\',\'sans-serif\'; mso-fareast-font-family: Arial; color: #0070c0;\">&nbsp;</span></strong><a style=\"color: #0662bb !important; text-decoration: underline !important; font-weight: 800 !important;\" href=\"https://immunisationhandbook.health.gov.au/contents/vaccine-preventable-diseases/hepatitis-a\" target=\"_blank\" >Health Gov Au Hepatitis A immunisation handbook </a></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"line-height: normal; margin: 5.0pt 0in 5.0pt 0in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 11.0pt; font-family: \'Arial\',\'sans-serif\'; mso-fareast-font-family: Arial; background: white;\">In <strong style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight: normal;\">Tasmania</strong>, the <strong style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight: normal;\">Hepatitis A vaccine</strong> is <strong style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight: normal;\">not mandatory</strong> for all healthcare workers, but it is required for specific high-risk roles. These roles include healthcare workers who are working in remote Indigenous communities, with Indigenous children, or in areas where sanitation is a concern.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"line-height: normal; margin: 5.0pt 0in 5.0pt 0in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 11.0pt; font-family: \'Arial\',\'sans-serif\'; mso-fareast-font-family: Arial; background: white;\">If you are working in these high-risk settings, it is recommended or required to receive the Hepatitis A vacc